-- CANADA RESEARCH ROUNDUP:- Canyon Services Group, Surge Energy
-- 
-- Tue Aug 05, 2014 06:04AM EDT
-- None



August 5 (Reuters) - Securities analysts revised their ratings and price targets on several Canadian companies, including Canyon Services Group and Surge Energy, on Tuesday.

HIGHLIGHTS * Canyon Services Group <FRC.TO>: CIBC raises to sector outperformer from sector performer * Surge Energy <SGY.TO>: Canaccord Genuity cuts to hold; raises target to C$8.50 from C$8.00Following is a summary of research actions on Canadian companies reported by Reuters on Tuesday. Stock entries are in alphabetical order.* Canadian Real Estate Investment <REF_u.TO>:CIBC ups target C$48 from C$47;sector performer * Canyon Services Group <FRC.TO>: CIBC raises to sector outperformer from sector performer  * Ecosynthetix Inc <ECO.TO>: Canaccord Genuity cuts target price to C$4 from C$5; rating buy * Fortis Inc <FTS.TO>: CIBC raises to sector outperformer; target price to C$37 from C$35  * Prometic Life Sciences Inc <PLI.TO>: Panmure starts with buy rating; target of C$1.95  * Rona Inc <RON.TO>: NBF raises target price to C$12 from C$11.50; rating sector perform  * Surge Energy <SGY.TO>: CIBC cuts to sector performer from sector outperformer  * Surge Energy <SGY.TO>: CIBC raises price target to C$9.50 from C$9